  <h2>The Most Common Reasons Houses Won't Sell</h2>
  <p>I've bought houses in every one of these situations. None of them are deal-breakers on my end.</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>The house needs too much work.</strong> Traditional buyers want move-in ready. I buy houses that need full rehabs — foundation issues, roof problems, outdated everything. Condition doesn't scare me off.</li>
    <li><strong>The price has to come down but you can't afford to.</strong> Sometimes after commissions, repairs, and closing costs, a traditional sale doesn't pencil out. With a direct sale there are no fees to eat into your proceeds.</li>
    <li><strong>A buyer fell through.</strong> Financing fell apart. Inspection turned up something they didn't want. The deal died at the last minute. Cash buyers don't have financing contingencies — when I say I'll close, I close.</li>
    <li><strong>The listing expired with no offers.</strong> That's a signal, not a death sentence. It usually means the house needs a different kind of buyer — one who isn't looking for a retail-ready property.</li>
    <li><strong>Probate, inherited property, or a complicated title.</strong> These are the situations traditional buyers walk away from. I work through them all the time.</li>
    <li><strong>You need to move faster than the market allows.</strong> Job relocation, divorce, financial pressure — when you need out in 2–3 weeks, a 60–90 day listing isn't an option.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The Honest Trade-Off</h2>
  <p>A direct cash offer will typically be below what you'd get in a perfect retail sale. That's the honest truth and I'd rather tell you upfront than have you find out later. What you're trading is maximum price for certainty, speed, and zero cost on your end.</p>
  <p>When you add up what a traditional sale actually costs — 5–6% in agent commissions, repair requests after inspection, holding costs for 2–3 months, and the real risk of a deal collapsing — a fair cash offer often puts more money in your pocket than the listing price suggests. But I'll always give you a straight comparison so you can make the call that's right for you.</p>
  <p>If the traditional route is actually the better move for your situation, I'll tell you that. I'm not here to talk you into anything.</p>

