  <h2>Questions I Get Asked All the Time</h2>

  <h3>How long is too long for a house to sit on the market?</h3>
  <p>In the Wichita market, most well-priced homes sell within 30–60 days. If you're past 90 days with no serious offers, the market is telling you something — usually that the price needs to come down significantly, the house needs work buyers aren't willing to take on, or both. At that point a direct sale is worth running the numbers on.</p>

  <h3>My listing just expired. Can I still sell to you?</h3>
  <p>Yes, and honestly that's one of the most common situations I deal with. An expired listing doesn't mean the house is unsellable — it usually means it wasn't the right fit for a traditional buyer. I buy houses that cash buyers can work with, regardless of what happened on the MLS.</p>

  <h3>A buyer backed out right before closing. What are my options?</h3>
  <p>You can relist, but you'll likely face the same inspection objections and financing risk again. Or you can call me. I pay cash, so there's no financing contingency and no lender that can kill the deal at the last minute. Once we have a signed contract, we close.</p>

  <h3>My house needs a lot of work. Does that matter to you?</h3>
  <p>Not the way it matters to a traditional buyer. I factor repair costs into my offer — I'm not going to ask you to fix the roof before we close. Deferred maintenance, outdated kitchens, foundation issues, water damage — I've bought houses in all of those conditions. The offer reflects what the house is worth as-is, not what it would be worth after a full renovation.</p>

  <h3>Will I get a fair price?</h3>
  <p>Fair and full retail aren't the same thing — I want to be straight with you about that. My offer is based on real Wichita comps and what I know it'll take to bring the house up to market condition. It won't be the number you'd get if the house were perfect and you had 90 days to wait for the right buyer. But when you subtract commissions, repair requests, carrying costs, and the risk of another deal falling apart — a lot of sellers end up in a similar place. I'll always show you the math so you can decide what makes sense.</p>

  <h3>What areas in Wichita do you buy in?</h3>
  <p>All of them. College Hill, Riverside, Delano, Eastside, Northeast Wichita, South Wichita — I've bought in every part of the city. I also buy in Andover, Derby, Maize, Goddard, Park City, Augusta, and El Dorado. If you're in the Wichita metro, reach out.</p>

  <h3>How fast can you actually close?</h3>
  <p>7 days is the fastest we can move through title. Most closes happen in 14–21 days. If you need more time — say you're coordinating a move or dealing with an estate — we can push the date out to whatever works for you. You're not locked into someone else's timeline.</p>

